description:
&lt;p&gt;Hosted by Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust (HHFT), we are looking for someone to join our system-wide Transformation Team. Working across North and Mid Hampshire the postholder will lead on the delivery of a varied and complex portfolio of component projects designed to deliver clear outcomes and financial and quality benefits to tight and defined timescales. These will transform patient care across the system requiring a significant and sustainable change in operational working practise.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ambitious programme of improvement work includes projects looking to transform intermediate, planned, primary, and urgent care as well as mental health provision. The postholder will be focused on one of these areas.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As well as delivering change across the local care system, the postholder will work closely with the Head of Transformation and Associate Director of Quality Improvement (QI) in HHFT to embed QI as the way we deliver change, and improve the QI capability of the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colin Williams - Head of Transformation&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Colin.williams@hhft.nhs.uk / 01256313050&lt;/p&gt;
